Title: Series: Theatrum Pictorium
Description: The Flight into Egypt. Landscape with the Holy Family on a road in the centre, the Virgin Mary and Jesus Christ on a donkey preceded by St Joseph, followed by a shepherd, other shepherds and trees in the background; after Tintoretto. c.1656-1660 Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Jan van Ossenbeeck
Intermediary draughtsman: David Teniers the Younger
Curator's comments: This is first state before number (from the first edition published in 1660), for second state see S.4589. This is one from 246 plates of Teniers' Theatre of Paintings, for comment on the series see 1850,0713.20.
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (67)
Weigel 1843 / Suppléments au Peintre-Graveur de Adam Bartsch (307.50)
Acquisition notes: For the history of the acquisition of the Sheepshanks collection, please see Sheepshanks.1
